WILLIAM SUMMERS, 357 acs.
Pittsylvania Co. on the Brs. of Sandy Cr;
adj. James Walker, Donalson & Lawless;
26 Oct 1779, p.39. A.C. of 40 Shill.
Sterl.

WILLIAM COTTRILL, 369 acs.
Pittsylvania Co. on Fall Cr., adj. Fowless;
26 Oct 1779, p.41. A.C. of £2 sterl.

JAMES FULTON, 220 acs. Pittsylvania
Co. on the Main Sandy Cr., adj. Dodson;
20 Oct 1779, p.90. A.C. of £1.85.

JOSEPH CALDWELL, 35 acs. by
Survey 20 Apr 1779 in Rockbridge Co.;
5 Jan 1780, p.185. A.C. of 5 Shill. Sterl.

JOSEPH GOODWIN, 39 acs. by Survey
16 Apr 1768 [Henry Co.] on Smiths Riv.;
10 Jun 1780, p.463. A.C. of 5 Shill. sterl.

MARK COLE, 245 acs. by Survey 11
Dec 1753 in Bedford Co. on the little Cr.;
4 Jul 1780, p.567. A.C. of 25 Shill. sterl.
